# linglib

![](https://img.shields.io/badge/version-0.1.3-red.svg)
![](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-prealpha-red.svg)
[![](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-000000.svg)](LICENSE)

linglib is a generic Python library for linguistics field. It contains several classes and function which will help developers with linguistic background/knowledge.

linglib is still in planning phase. Checkout coverage section for completed packages. Also library does not have any documentation yet. Feel free to use `help()` to see builtin docstrings.

## Requirements

 - Python 3.3 or higher
